The late struggle icon's family have invited the public to line the streets from the Kupane Funeral Parlour from 2 o'clock where her body will be transported to her house for the last time. JOHANNESBURG - More people are arriving at the late Winnie Madikizela-Mandela's home in Orlando west ahead of a guard of honour  due to take place on Friday afternoon. The late struggle icon's family have invited the public to line the streets from the Kupane Funeral Parlour from 2 o'clock where her body will be transported to her house for the last time. Madikizela-Mandela will be laid to rest at a Fourways cemetery on Saturday after her official funeral at the Orlando Stadium. Meanwhile, police are investigating an alleged plot to disrupt the funeral procession of Winnie Madikizela-Mandela. There are reports that a group of people are trying to disrupt the motorcade. The reasons for the planned disruptions are still unknown. 